  <bodyText><![CDATA[<p><img src="/media/13088429/testing-packages.jpeg" alt="" data-udi="umb://media/55aef682d9d9488e961d1b8cc0a2c209" /></p>
<p>We frequently review the below information with testing suppliers to ensure you continue to receive peace of mind when planning your holiday. However, due to the constantly evolving nature of the Coronavirus pandemic and the potential for changes to travel testing requirements, changes can occur at short notice following new developments, relevant guidance and legal obligations.</p>
<p><strong>How do I know what Covid-19 test/s I need?</strong></p>
<p>The Covid-19 test package and supplier you require depends on the entry requirements of your holiday destination and the UK country you live in – check the requirements for <a data-udi="umb://document/504132b8d7ab4765a76479fc557c5cb4" href="/{localLink:umb://document/504132b8d7ab4765a76479fc557c5cb4}#TravelAdviceperCountry" title="Entry Requirements" data-anchor="#TravelAdviceperCountry">the country you’re travelling to</a> and from before booking your test package. The testing suppliers will be able to give you more advice. Please note the requirements when travelling to and from <a rel="nofollow noopener" href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/red-amber-and-green-list-rules-for-entering-england" target="_blank">England</a>, <a rel="nofollow noopener" href="https://www.nidirect.gov.uk/information-and-services/coronavirus-covid-19/travel-advice-and-guidance" target="_blank">Northern Ireland</a>, <a rel="nofollow noopener" href="https://www.gov.scot/publications/coronavirus-covid-19-international-travel-quarantine/pages/red-amber-and-green-list-countries/" target="_blank">Scotland</a> and <a rel="nofollow noopener" href="https://gov.wales/rules-foreign-travel-and-wales-coronavirus-covid-19" target="_blank">Wales</a> may be different.</p>
<p>If requirements in the UK or your destination country change before travel, you may need to make new testing arrangements.</p>
<p><strong>Supplier Testing Packages and Discounts</strong></p>
<p>UK government listed Covid-19 test suppliers <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.expresstest.co.uk/?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan" target="_blank" data-anchor="?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan">ExpressTest</a>, <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.randoxhealth.com/" target="_blank">Randox</a> and <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.projectscreen.co.uk/" target="_blank">Prenetics</a> provide Covid-19 tests for travel <strong>before your holiday, on your holiday or when you return</strong> easier and aim to make testing more affordable, should the requirements change. Each supplier has several different types of testing packages available. Please check which package you will need, depending on your COVID-19 vaccination status and country entry requirements:</p>
<p><strong>Please check your phone/handset type meets the requirement of the test company you have selected</strong></p>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.randoxhealth.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Randox Testing Packages</strong></a></p>
<p>Randox provide Lateral Flow &amp; PCR testing, for both departing from and arriving back into the UK.</p>
<p>For further information, visit <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.randoxhealth.com/" target="_blank">Randox</a>, select the Covid-19 test most suited to your needs.</p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.expresstest.co.uk/?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan" target="_blank" data-anchor="?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan"><strong>ExpressTest Testing Packages</strong></a></p>
<p>Express Test offer tests at 23 sites, for travellers arriving in England at various UK locations. <span style="font-weight: 400;">Express Test also offer the return to UK Antigen Lateral Flow Test</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<p>For further information, visit <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.expresstest.co.uk/?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan" target="_blank" data-anchor="?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan">ExpressTest</a>, select the Covid-19 test most suited to your needs.</p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><a rel="noopener" href="https://www.projectscreen.co.uk/" target="_blank"><strong>Prenetics Testing Packages</strong></a></p>
<p>Prenetics provide Lateral Flow &amp; PCR testing, for both departing from and arriving back into the UK.</p>
<p>For further information, visit <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.projectscreen.co.uk/" target="_blank">Prenetics</a>, select the Covid-19 test most suited to your needs.</p>
</div>
<p>We understand that due to the nature of the ongoing updates to the UK government’s requirements to travel and the variance in requirements from country to county, you may still have questions about Covid-19 testing for travel. If you would like more information about the testing requirements for your holiday, the Covid-19 testing suppliers can offer further advice and clarity on the test packages you may require. Please visit <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.expresstest.co.uk/?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan" target="_blank" data-anchor="?utm_source=hotelplan&amp;utm_medium=website&amp;utm_campaign=hotelplan">ExpressTest</a>, <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.randoxhealth.com/" target="_blank">Randox</a> or <a rel="noopener" href="https://www.projectscreen.co.uk/" target="_blank">Prenetics</a> for more details. You can also view the current <a rel="nofollow noopener" href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/coronavirus-covid-19-testing-for-people-travelling-to-england" target="_blank">UK Government’s minimum testing requirements on their website</a>.</p>
<p>If you have would like to know more about the extra measure’s we’ve put in place to help keep you and your money safe, you can find our <strong>In Safe Hands promise </strong><a data-udi="umb://document/fa72be9e45bc442089252c6a18a0d2ae" href="/{localLink:umb://document/fa72be9e45bc442089252c6a18a0d2ae}" title="In Safe Hands">here</a> or our <a data-udi="umb://document/ea588978885c4203b4e35f12af49054c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ea588978885c4203b4e35f12af49054c}" title="Coronavirus">travel advice and guidance in relation to Covid-19 here</a>.</p>
<p>We would highly recommend that you review your travel insurance and take out additional Covid-19 travel insurance. Some travel insurance policies do not cover you as standard if your holiday is disrupted due to coronavirus, but there are new policies and add-ons appearing on the market that will cover for any unforeseen circumstances between booking and departing on holiday as well as while on holiday.</p>
<p>Our insurance partner, Campbell Irvine offer travel insurance with additional comprehensive Covid-19 cover and will be happy to give you a quote. To contact them, please visit <a rel="noopener" href="https://campbellirvinedirect.com/inghamswinter/" target="_blank" title="Campbell Irvine Direct Winter Insurance">here</a> for winter trips and <a rel="noopener" href="https://campbellirvinedirect.com/inghamssummer/" target="_blank" title="Campbell Irvine Direct Summer Insurance">here</a> for summer.</p>
<p>Testing services are supplied by third parties, and not Inghams, they are not part of our product, linked travel arrangement or package. Inghams are not responsible for any part of the testing or any impact this may have on your ability to travel.</p>]]></bodyText>
